{
  "text": "Analysis. During scarification process, three blood samples were immediately withdrawn from the vena cava of each rat and used for blood coagulation, hematology, and biochemical analyses. The first sample was collected on a tube contained 0.11 M sodium citrate anticoagulant (1 : 9, v : v) and used for plasma preparation for screening of the following blood coagulation tests: prothrombin time (PT), activated partial thromboplastin time (APTT), and fibrinogen concentrations (FIB), by using Dade Behring reagents and following manufacturer's instructions as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
